<dl id="jn1018h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="jn1" href="#jn1018">JN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/jn1all.htm#jn1018h"> (NLI.2A) 18(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Peter Lombard: / Four Books of Sentences <p class="spbr">&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;</a> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Peter Lombard (1096-1160), his <cite>Sententiarum libri IV</cite> (1148-1151) has four parts, translated as <cite>The Mystery of the Trinity</cite>; <cite>On Creation</cite>; <cite>On the Incarnation of the Word</cite>; and <cite>The Doctrine of Signs</cite>. </mm> </dd></dl>
